SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 789
By Seal
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Parker Newman of
Sevier County High School on being named the
Region 1-5A Athlete of the Year.
WHEREAS, we are pleased to specially honor and commend those successful high
school athletes who, through their magnificent exploits, bring honor to the State of Tennessee
and serve as exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable athlete is Parker Newman of Sevier County High
School, a football player of extraordinary talent, skill, and athleticism, who has been named the
Region 1-5A Athlete of the Year; and
WHEREAS, a gifted receiver, Parker Newman posted 1,059 receiving yards and caught
10 touchdown passes this past season for the Bears; and
WHEREAS, a monster on the defensive side of the ball, Parker Newman recorded 117
tackles, three sacks, and four interceptions; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Newman epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as he has
achieved a high level of success in sports while evincing great character both on and off the
field; and
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that we recognize and commend this elite athlete and
outstanding young gentleman; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Parker Newman of
Sevier County High School on being named the Region 1-5A Athlete of the Year and extend to
him our best wishes for much continued success in his future endeavors.
